Zombie bite. So here’s the final product and back story. In an effort to help a family member going through breast cancer I wanted do something to try and help with all the extra expenses that she’s being hit with. 100% of the money raised from these is going to her and then after she gets all fixed up we will continue to donate a portion to a breast cancer foundation. They are $85 plus shipping if interested please send me a DM for a shipping quote. Coming off our biggest Transworld to date with also a fairly large wholesale order waiting to be finished I may have been just a little overzealous when I jumped into this project.  Poor old Vincent Brimstone got started and then quickly forgotten. I do love WED clay, but on big projects like Vincent I don’t always sculpt fast enough and this is the outcome. Honestly I felt like I had rushed the frame and didn’t love the shape the body was taking so I’ll start over. I’ll do a little re-bend and bulk up the frame before adding the clay, and maybe this time I’ll use monster clay #damn #it #dry #clay #sculpture #sculpting #art #evillejs #evillejscreepycloset #evansville
